The paper deals with communication protocols in the presence of an eavesdropper, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of networks and links suggests a focus on networking (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC), but the paper specifically mentions parallel-link networks, which is more specific and may fall under the category of computer communications (cs.CC). Finally, the notion of hidability and its relationship to information-theoretic secrecy suggests a possible connection to security and privacy (cs.SI).
